1. Design Philosophy
Core Principles
Slack-native first.


Minimal cognitive load.


Safe by default.


Intelligent but non-intrusive.


No AI gimmicks.


Enterprise-clean aesthetic.


Settings power hidden but accessible.



2. Design System Foundation
Visual Style
Tone:
 • Professional
 • Calm
 • Intelligent
 • Not playful
 • Not futuristic
Inspiration:
 Linear × Notion × Slack × Vercel

Color Palette
Primary:
 Deep indigo / slate
Accent:
 Soft electric blue
Status Colors:
 Green – success
 Amber – review required
 Red – sensitive detected
 Gray – inactive
Background:
 Very light gray (#F7F8FA range)
Cards:
 White with soft border (#E5E7EB style)

Typography
Primary:
 Inter
Hierarchy:
H1 – 28px / semibold
 H2 – 22px / semibold
 H3 – 18px / medium
 Body – 14px
 Meta – 12px
Slack UI uses Slack-native formatting.

3. Information Architecture
Primary Surfaces:
Slack Bot (Primary)


Web Dashboard (Secondary)



4. Slack UI Design PRD
Slack is NOT visually designed — but interactions are.

4.1 Slack Insight Notification
Bot Message Layout:
Title:
 “New Insight Detected”
Body:
 Short structured summary:
• Source: Zoom Call
 • Confidence: High
 • Sensitivity: Moderate
 • Insight: Removing onboarding step reduced friction
Actions:
[ Generate Draft ]
 [ Save Internal ]
 [ Ignore ]

4.2 Draft Modal (Slack Modal)
Modal Structure:
Header:
 Generate Draft
Section 1: Insight Summary (read-only, collapsible)
Section 2: Draft Selector
Radio:
 • Educational
 • Tactical
 • Reflective
Textarea:
 Editable draft
Footer:
[ Cancel ]
 [ Publish ]
 [ Save as Internal ]
If sensitive content detected:
Warning banner:
 “Sensitive data masked. Review before publishing.”

4.3 Slack Settings Shortcut
Slash command:
 /arc-settings
Opens dashboard link.

5. Dashboard Design PRD

5.1 Layout Structure
Left Sidebar:
 • Overview
 • Insights
 • Sources
 • Sensitivity Controls
 • Tone Profile
 • Publishing
 • Billing
 • Audit Logs
Top Bar:
 Workspace name
 Plan badge
 User avatar
Main Panel:
 Context-dependent

6. Overview Page
Purpose:
 High-level system health.
Sections:
Recent Insights (last 7 days)


Insights Generated


Drafts Pending


Published Posts


Sensitivity Flags Triggered


Cards:
 Minimal, clean, small charts optional.

7. Insights Page
Table Layout:
Columns:
 • Date
 • Source
 • Confidence
 • Sensitivity
 • Status
 • Action
Clicking opens side drawer.
Side Drawer Shows:
• Full structured insight
 • Related sources
 • Generate draft button
 • Mark internal only

8. Sources Page
Card-based layout.
Each integration card:
Slack
 Zoom
 Google Workspace
 Gmail
Each card shows:
Status:
 Connected / Not Connected
Settings Button

Source Settings Modal
Slack:
 • Select channels
 • Toggle auto-ingestion
 • Retention period
Zoom:
 • Auto process transcripts toggle
 • Process only recorded calls toggle
Google Workspace:
 • Folder selection UI
 • Monitor specific docs toggle
Gmail:
 • Label selection dropdown
 • Sender whitelist

9. Sensitivity Controls Page
This is critical UX.
Layout:
 Grouped toggle switches.
Section: Numeric Data
• Allow percentages
 • Allow revenue numbers
 • Mask metrics above threshold
Section: Names
• Allow personal names
 • Allow client names
 • Allow company names
Section: Strategic Info
• Mask roadmap items
 • Mask internal tool references
Redaction Strictness Slider:
Low — Moderate — High
Real-time preview panel:
Example draft shown with masking preview.

10. Tone Profile Page
Radio-based selection:
Default Tone:
 • Educational
 • Tactical
 • Reflective
 • Contrarian
Optional:
 Custom voice notes textarea.

11. Publishing Page
Connected Accounts:
LinkedIn
Status:
 Connected / Reconnect
Settings:
 • Default visibility
 • Default hashtags on/off
 • Schedule future publishing toggle

12. Billing Page
Plan Card:
 • Current Plan
 • Usage this month
 • Upgrade button
Dodo embedded checkout modal.
Usage Bar:
 Insights generated / limit

13. Audit Logs Page
Enterprise-style simple table:
• Action
 • User
 • Timestamp
 • Source
Important for trust.

14. Empty States
Insights Page Empty:
Headline:
 “No insights yet.”
Subtext:
 “Insights are generated automatically from connected sources.”
CTA:
 Connect Source

15. Loading States
Use skeleton loaders.
 Never spinner-only screens.

16. Error States
If AI fails:
Slack:
 “Insight extraction failed. Retry?”
Dashboard:
 Retry button.
If LinkedIn publish fails:
Show exact API error message.
 Retry button.

17. Edge Cases
Case: High sensitivity detected
Slack:
 Require explicit confirmation checkbox before publish.
Case: Low confidence insight
Slack:
 “Confidence low. Generate anyway?”
Case: No transcript available
Show:
 “Transcript not available for this call.”

18. Mobile Responsiveness
Dashboard fully responsive.
Slack remains primary surface.

